notes
PIs: Yoshizumi Miyoshi, Kazuo Shiokawa, Shin-ichiro Oyama (ISEE), Esa Turunen (SGO)

This experiment focuses on causality to produce hard-particle precipitation and
its effects on the ionosphere, thermosphere, and atmosphere from midnight after
substorm onset to the late morning. VHF (vertical manda) collaborates with
optical instruments at the site. Auroral activity in the clear sky is desirable.


The requested experiment windows using NI(21) and FI(20) are:
Jan 12: 2330-2400 (0.5 hr)
Jan 13: 0000-1030 (10.5 hrs)
Jan 14: 0000-1000 (10 hrs)
Jan 15: 0000-1000 (10 hrs)
Jan 16: 0000-1000 (10 hrs) 
